INSERT INTO `recipe` VALUES (1,'Khaman Dhokla','1) Take gram flour in a bowl. Add yogurt and approximately one cup of warm water and mix. Avoid lumps. Add salt and mix again.\n 2) Leave it aside to ferment for three to four hours. When gram flour mixture has fermented, add turmeric powder and green chilli-ginger paste. Mix. Heat the steamer. Grease a thali.\n 3) In a small bowl take lemon juice, soda bicarbonate, one teaspoon of oil and mix. Add it to the batter and whisk briskly. Pour batter into the greased thali and place it in the steamer.\n 4) Cover with the lid and steam for ten minutes. When a little cool, cut into squares and keep in a serving bowl/plate. \n 5)Heat remaining oil in a small pan. Add mustard seeds. When the seeds begin to crackle, remove and pour over the dhoklas.\n 6)Serve, garnished with chopped coriander leaves and scraped coconut.','1) Gram flour (besan) sieved - 2 cups\n2) Yogurt beaten - 1 cup\n3) Salt to taste\n4) Turmeric powder - 1/2 teaspoon\n5) Green chilli-ginger paste - 1 teaspoon\n6) Oil - 2 tablespoons\n7) Lemon juice - 1 tablespoon\n8) Soda bicarbonate - 1 teaspoon\n9)Mustard seeds - 1 teaspoon\n10)Fresh coriander leaves chopped - 2 tablespoons\n11) Coconut scraped - 1/2 cup',_binary 'E:\\Workspace\\Java Mini Project\\bin\\Pictures\\Dhokla.jpeg','1)Calories : 1446 Kcal\n2)Carbohydrates : 137.7 gm\n3)Protein : 53 gm\n4)Fat : 76.2 gm\n5)Other : 38.7gm',NULL),(2,'Choco Lava Cake','1) Preheat the oven to 180°C/350°F/Gas Mark 4. Grease the muffin moulds, dust with flour and remove excess flour.\n2) Put the chocolate in a microwave-safe bowl, add the butter and melt in the microwave oven on HIGH for one minute. Remove the bowl from oven and stir the contents briskly. Break the eggs into another bowl. Add powdered sugar and blend with a hand blender till light and frothy. Sift the cocoa powder directly in the mixture and mix.\n3) Add the melted chocolate-butter mixture and mix. Sift the flour and baking powder directly into the bowl and blend with the hand blender till smooth. Pour the batter into the muffin moulds, taking care not to fill up to the top.\n4)Place the moulds in the preheated oven and bake for seven to eight minutes. Take the moulds out of the oven, loosen the edges carefully with a knife. Carefully unmould the cakes onto a serving plate and serve hot.','1) Plain chocolate (broken) - 125 grams\n2) Cocoa powder 1 tbsp + for dusting\n3) Refined flour (maida) 1/2 cup + for dusting\n4) Unsalted butter 9 tbsps + for greasing\n5) Eggs 4\nPowdered sugar 6 tablespoons\nBaking powder 1/2 teaspoon',_binary 'E:\\Workspace\\Java Mini Project\\bin\\Pictures\\Choco lava cake.jpeg','1) Calories : 2426 Kcal\n2) Carbohydrates : 156.1 gm\n3) Protein : 44.4 gm\n4) Fat : 180.4 gm\n5) Other : 0',NULL),(3,'Chocolate Oreo Cake','A) How to prepare oreo cake in a steamer:\n1) Firstly, take 300 grams oreo biscuit in the mixi and blend to a fine powder. you can use any cream biscuit of your choice.\n2) Transfer the powdered biscuit into a large bowl.\n3) Add 1 cup milk and mix using the whisk.\n4) Mix until a smooth lump-free batter is formed adding milk if required.\n5) Just before steaming, add ½ tsp eno fruit salt and mix gently adding 2 tbsp of milk. you can alternatively use ¼ tsp baking soda or ½ tsp baking powder.\n6) Pour the batter into a bowl. make sure to grease the bowl and line with parchment paper.\n7) Place the bowl into steamer and steam for 45 minutes.\n8) Steam until the toothpick inserted comes out clean. make sure to keep an eye, as water in steamer may reduce.\n9) Unmould the cake and cool completely.\nB) How to make the chocolate glaze:\n1) Firstly, in a glass bowl take 200 grams of dark chocolate chips. you can alternatively use chopped chocolate here.\n2) Pour in 100 grams of hot whipping cream.\n3) Stir and melt the chocolate chips completely. you can microwave or use double boiler method if your chocolate is not melting completely.\n4) Silky shiny chocolate mirror glaze is ready to decorate. make sure the glaze is not too hot.\n5) Pour the glaze immediately over the cake.\n6) Finally, eggless oreo chocolate cake ready to enjoy decorated with strawberry.','1) 900 grams oreo biscuit\n2) 3.75 cup milk\n3) 1.5 tsp eno fruit salt\nfor chocolate glaze:\n4) 600 grams dark chocolate chips\n5) 3 cup cream (hot)',_binary 'E:\\Workspace\\Java Mini Project\\bin\\Pictures\\Oreo cake.jpeg','1)Calories 336 \n2)Calories from Fat 0\n3)Total Fat9.8 g 15.1%\n4)Saturated Fat3.6 g 18%\n5)Cholesterol0.1 mg 0.03%\n6)Sodium445.4 mg18.6%\n7)Total Carbohydrates58.2 g 19.4%',NULL),(4,'Veg Spring Roll','A) How to prepare spring roll wrapper:\n1) Firstly, in a large bowl take 2 cup maida, 2 tbsp corn flour and ½ tsp salt.\n2) Add 2½ cup water and mix well using a whisk.\n3) Whisk until a smooth lump-free batter is formed adding water as required.\n4) Now grease the pan and pour a ladleful of batter on a hot pan.\n5) Swirl once making sure the batter is uniformly spread.\n6) Cook for a minute or until the sheet is cooked without browning.\n7) Now flip over gently and continue to cook.\n8) Finally, spring roll wrapper is ready. you can cover and use to prepare patti samosa or spring rolls.\nB) how to prepare veg stuffing:\n1) Firstly, in a large wok, heat 2 tbsp oil. saute 3 clove garlic, 2 chilly and 2 tbsp spring onion.\n2) Add ½ onion and stir fry on high flame.\n3) Now add 1 carrot, 2 cup cabbage, 5 beans, ½ capsicum.\n4) Stir fry without losing the crunchiness of vegetables.\n5) Further, add 2 tbsp vinegar, 2 tbsp soy sauce, 2 tsp chilly sauce, ¼ tsp pepper powder and ½ tsp salt.\n6) Mix well making sure everything is well combined. stuffing is ready.\nC) How to fold and fry spring roll:\n1) Firstly, take a prepared wrapper and place a tbsp of prepared veg stuffing.\n2) Rub a tsp of maida paste around the edge. maida helps to seal the roll.\n3) Now roll and fold the sides making sure the roll is sealed tight.\n4) Deep fry in hot oil, keeping the flame on low.\n5) Stir occasionally, until the roll turns golden brown and crisp.\n6) Drain off removing excess oil.\n7)Finally, enjoy veg spring roll with sweet chilly sauce.','A) for sheet / wrapper:\n1) 6 cup maida / plain flour\n2) 6 tbsp corn flour\n3) 1.5 tsp salt\n4) 7.5 cup water\nB) for stuffing:\n1) 6 tbsp oil\n2) 9 clove garlic (finely chopped)\n3) 6 chilli (finely chopped)\n4) 6 tbsp spring onion (chopped)\n5) 1.5 onion (sliced)\n6) 3 carrot (julienne)\n7) 6 cup cabbage (chopped)\n8) 15 beans (chopped)\n9) 1.5 capsicum (chopped)\n10) 6 tbsp vinegar\n11) 6 tbsp soy sauce\n12) 6 tsp chilli sauce\n13) 0.75 tsp pepper powder\n14) 1.5 tsp salt\nC) Other ingredients:\n1) 1.5 cup maida paste (for sealing)\n2) oil (for frying)',_binary 'E:\\Workspace\\Java Mini Project\\bin\\Pictures\\spring rolls.jpeg','1)Calories 690\n2)Calories from Fat 670\n3)Total Fat74 g 113.8%\n4)Saturated Fat5 g 25%\n5)Sodium100 mg4.2%\n6)Total Carbohydrates7 g 2.3%\n7)Protein2 g 4%',NULL),(5,'Rasmalai','A) Chenna / paneer recipe:\n1) Firstly, in a thick bottomed pan add 1 litre cows milk. make sure to use cows milk, else rasmalai will not be soft and juicy.\n2) Furthermore, stir occasionally and get to a boil.\n3) Additionally, add lemon juice and stir well.\n4) Add more lemon juice and stir till milk curdles completely.\n5) And immediately drain the curdled milk into the hand kerchief / cheese cloth.\n6) Pour a cup of water and clean the paneer as it has lemon juice in it.\n7) Furthermore, bring it together and squeeze off excess water.\n8) Hang for 30 minutes. or till all the water drains off completely.\n9)After 30 minutes, start to knead the paneer for 10 minutes.\n10) Knead paneer till it turns out smooth without any grains of milk. else there will be cracks on rasmalai and will break while boiling in sugar syrup.\n11)Furthermore, make small balls and flatten. keep aside.\n\nB) Sugar syrup recipe:\n1) Firstly, in a deep vessel take 1½ cup of sugar.\n2) Furthermore, add 8 glasses of water and stir well.\n3) Boil the syrup for 10 minutes on medium flame.\n4) After that, drop the prepared flattened paneer balls into boiling sugar syrup.\n5) Cover and boil for 15 minutes. the flattened paneer balls will have doubled in size.\n6) Furthermore, with a help of slotted spoon take each rasmalai and squeeze of sugar syrup.\n7) Allow all the squeezed paneer balls to cool completely. or till they come to room temperature.\n\nC) Rabri / Rabdi recipe:\n1) Firstly, in a large nonstick pan heat milk.\n2) Furthermore, stir occasionally and get to a boil.\n3) Reduce the flame to medium. and once a layer of cream is formed over the milk, stick it to sides of vessel.\n4) Further, get the milk to boil again.\n5) And repeat the gathering of cream to sides of kadai.\n6) Repeat the process for atleast 5 times or till milk reduces to one-third.\n7) Further, add sugar.\n8) Also add cardamom powder and saffron milk.\n9) Give a good mix and get the milk again to boil.\n10) Also scrape off the collected cream from sides. and give a good stir.\n11) Transfer to a bowl and let it attain to room temperature.\n12) Further, refrigerate for 2-3 hours before adding to rasmalai.\n13) Finally, rasmalai is ready to be served.','A) Rasmalai for chenna / paneer:\n1) 3 litre milk (full cream cows milk)\n2) 6 tbsp lemon juice\n3) 3 cup water\nB) for sugar syrup:\n1) 4.5 cup sugar\n2) 24 cups water\nC) For rabri / rabdi:\n1) 3 litre milk (full cream cows / buffalo milk)\n2) 0.75 cup sugar\n3) 1.5 tsp cardamom powder\n3) 6 tbsp saffron milk\n4) 21 pistachios (chopped)\n5) 15 almonds (chopped)\n6) 30 cashews (chopped)',_binary 'E:\\Workspace\\Java Mini Project\\bin\\Pictures\\Rasmalai.jpeg','1)Calories 157\n2)Calories from Fat 0\n3)Total Fat3.7 g 5.7%\n4)Saturated Fat1.8 g 9%\n5)Cholesterol33.3 mg 11.1%\n6)Sodium167.7 mg7%\n7)Total Carbohydrates22.5 g 7.5%',NULL),(6,'Masala Dosa','1) Prepare the batter and ferment overnight:\nMasala Dosa is one of the most popular South Indian delicacies. To prepare the batter for Masala Dosa, wash and soak the rice (with fenugreek added into it) and urad dal in separate containers for approximately 6-8 hours. Once the rice and urad dal are soaked well, grind them separately in a mixer using the water in which they were soaked, till the mixture reaches a smooth consistency. Mix the batter of both the ingredients in a bigger container and add salt to it. Combine well and allow it to ferment overnight.\n2) Prepare the potato filling for Masala Dosa:\nTo prepare the filling of the dosa, heat 2 tbsp oil in a thick-bottomed pan and let the mustard seeds splutter. Then, add sliced onions, curry leaves, green chillies and sault them till the onions turn pink. Then, add a pinch of salt, turmeric powder and mix them well. Now, take the cubed potatoes and add them to the sauteed onions and mix them together. Pour water gradually into the mixture and allow the potatoes to simmer for around 4 minutes. When the mixture is in semi-thick state, turn off the gas and let it rest for a few seconds.\n3) Pan fry your dosa on a dosa tawa:\nNow, take a dosa tawa and heat it on low-medium flame. Smear 1 tsp oil on it to prepare the dosa. When the tawa is hot, pour and spread the batter evenly in a circular motion.','1) 2 cup parboiled rice\n2) 1/2 cup urad dal\n3) 1 teaspoon salt\n4) 1/4 cup refined oil\n5) 1/2 teaspoon fenugreek seeds\n6) 1/2 kilograms boiled potato\n7) 2 medium chopped green chilli\n8) 1 tablespoon mustard seeds\n9) 1/4 teaspoon turmeric\nsalt as required\n10) 1 1/2 cup sliced onion\n11) 2 tablespoon refined oil\n12) 10 leaves curry leaves\n13) 1/4 cup water',_binary 'E:\\Workspace\\Java Mini Project\\bin\\Pictures\\masala dosa.jpeg','1)Calories204\n2)Calories from Fat 33\n3)Total Fat3.7 g 5.7%\n4)Saturated Fat0.5 g 2.5%\n5)Sodium8.8 mg0.4%\n6)Total Carbohydrates37 g 12.3%\n7)Protein6.5 g 13%',NULL),(7,'Pav Bhaji','1) Heat a pan, add 1 tsp oil, 1/4 tsp jeera, 1/2 tsp ginger garlic paste, 1/4 cup chopped onion and saute it well.\n2) Then add 1/4 tsp salt, 1/4 cup chopped bottle gourd, 2 tbsp boiled peas, 3 tbsp chopped cauliflower, water as required, 1/2 tsp haldi, saute them well.\n3) Then add 1/4 cup boiled and diced potato, saute well. Add water as required and cover with lid & cook for 5 minutes.\n4) Remove the lid, mash the bhaji with a masher.\n5) Add 1/2 cup chopped tomato,1 tbsp pav bhaji masala, 1 tbsp red chilli powder, 1 tsp dhania powder, 1/4 tsp amchur powder,1 tsp butter, mix and mash well.\n6) Then Add 2 tbsp chopped capsicum, mix and mash it well. Cover with lid, cook for 5 minutes. Mash them well again.\n7) Garnish it with 1 tbsp chopped coriander leaves, mix it well.\n8) Serve it hot with pav and chopped onions.','1) 1/2 Chopped Cup(78.0 gm) Tomato\n2) 1/4 Chopped Cup(28.0 gm) Onion\n3) 1/4 Boiled Diced Cup(45.0 gm) Potato\n4) 1/4 Chopped Cup(26.0 gm) Bottle Gourd\n5) 1/4 Chopped Cup(26.0 gm) Cauliflower\n6) 1/4 Chopped Cup(36.0 gm) Capsicum\n7) 1/4 Boiled Cup(39.0 gm) Peas\n8) 1.0 Chopped Tbsp(3.0 gm) Coriander Leaves\n9) 2.0 Tbsp(13.0 gm) Pav Bhaji Masala\n10) 1.0 Powder Tsp(2.0 gm) Red Chilly\n11) 1.0 Tsp(4.0 gm) Butter\n12) 1.0 Tsp(2.0 gm) Dhania Powder\n13) 1/2 Tsp(3.0 gm) Ginger Garlic Paste\n14) 1/2 Tsp(1.0 gm) Haldi\n15) 1/4 Tsp(0.59 gm) Jeera\n16) 1/4 Tsp(0.53 gm) Dry Mango Powder\n17) 1/2 Tsp(2.0 gm) Salt\n18) 1.0 Tsp(3.0 ml) Oil\n19) 200.0 ml Water\n20) 6.0 Number(286.0 gm) Pav',_binary 'E:\\Workspace\\Java Mini Project\\bin\\Pictures\\pav bhaji.jpeg','1)Calories 100 \n2)Calories from Fat 45\n3)Total Fat5 g 7.7%\n4)Saturated Fat4 g 20%\n5)Sodium450 mg18.8%\n6)Total Carbohydrates11 g 3.7%\n7)Protein2 g 4%',NULL),(8,'Veg Momos','1) In a bowl, add 2 tbsp whole wheat flour, 1 tbsp maida, 1/8 tsp salt, water and knead into a soft dough.\n2) For stuffing:\nHeat 1 tsp oil in a kadai, add 1 tbsp chopped garlic, 1/2 tsp grated ginger, 1 tbsp chopped onion,1/2 tsp green chilly paste and saute until golden brown.\n3) Add 1 tbsp grated carrot,1 tbsp grated cabbage,1 tbsp chopped spring onion, 1/8 tsp salt,1/4 tsp black pepper powder and mix.\n4) Close the lid and cook for 5 min on low flame.\n5) Roll out dough into circular shape, fill the stuffing and seal.\n6) Heat oil for frying and deep fry momos till golden brown.','1) 2 Julienne Tbsp(12.0 gm) Cabbage\n2) 2 Chopped Tbsp(8.0 gm) Spring Onion\n3) 1 Chopped Tbsp(8.0 gm) Onion\n4) 1 Chopped Tbsp(8.0 gm) Garlic\n5) 1 Grated Tbsp(9.0 gm) Carrot\n6) 1 Grated Tbsp(10.0 gm) Paneer\n7) 1/2 Grated Tsp(0.94 gm) Ginger\n8) 1/2 Tsp(2.0 gm) Green Chilly Paste\n9) 1/4 Powder Tsp(0.75 gm) Black Pepper\n10) 1/8 Tsp(0.29 gm) Haldi\n11) 1/8 Tsp(0.54 gm) Salt\n12) 1 Tsp(3.0 ml) Oil\n13) 2 Tbsp(12.0 ml) Oil\n14) 15 ml Water\n16) 2 Tbsp(13.0 gm) Wheat Flour (Whole)\n17) 1 Tbsp(7.0 gm) Maida\n18) 0.13 Tsp(0.56 gm) Salt\n19) 10 ml Water',_binary 'E:\\Workspace\\Java Mini Project\\bin\\Pictures\\momos.jpeg','1)Calories 535\n2)Total Fat1.9 g 2.9%\n3)Saturated Fat0.3 g 1.5%\n4)Sodium70.7 mg2.9%\n5)Total Carbohydrates113.4 g 37.8%\n6)Protein16.3 g 32.6%',NULL),(9,'Butter Chicken','1) Bring a kettle of water to a boil. Place the cashews in a bowl and add enough boiling water to cover. Soak for 30 minutes.\n2) Heat 2 tablespoons of the ghee in an Instant Pot using the Sauté setting. Add the chicken, shallots, and onion and sauté for 8 minutes, until the chicken is browned and the onion is translucent. Add the remaining 4 tablespoons ghee, the tomato puree, tomato paste, lemon juice, garlic, cardamom, cinnamon stick, bay leaves, ginger, garam masala, cumin, salt, turmeric, and fenugreek and stir to combine. Secure the lid and select the meat/stew setting, or select the Pressure Cook and Manual setting and cook at high pressure for 10 minutes.\n3) Meanwhile, drain the cashews, rinse, and drain again. Combine the cashews and 3/4 cup water in a blender. Blend on high speed until very smooth and creamy, about 30 seconds in a high-speed blender, or 1 minute in a conventional blender.\n4) When the Instant Pot timer is done, quick release the pressure and stir in the cashew cream. Spoon the butter chicken into serving bowls. Sprinkle with almonds and cilantro and serve with naan on the side.\n5) RECIPE NOTES\n Tidbits: Repurpose any leftover sauce by adding it to some sautéed vegetables and rotisserie chicken or cooked shrimp for a quick dinner the next day.','1) 1/2 cup whole raw cashews\n2) 6 tablespoons ghee or unsalted grass-fed butter\n3) 3 pounds boneless skinless chicken thighs trimmed of fat and cut into 2-inch cubes\n4) 2 shallots chopped (about 1/2 cup)\n5) 1/2 yellow onion chopped\n6) 1 cup tomato puree\n7) 3/4 cup tomato paste\n8) 3 tablespoons freshly squeezed\n9) lemon juice\n10) 4 cloves garlic minced\n11) 6 green cardamom pods bruised with the butt of a knife\n12) 1 cinnamon stick\n13) 2 bay leaves\n14) 3 tablespoons Ginger peeled and minced\n15) 2 1/2 tablespoons garam masala\n16) 1 tablespoon ground cumin\n17) 1 tablespoon fine sea salt\n18) 2 teaspoons ground turmeric\n19) 1 teaspoon fenugreek seeds\n20) Toasted slivered almonds for garnish\n21) chopped fresh cilantro for garnish\n22) Garlic Naan for serving',_binary 'E:\\Workspace\\Java Mini Project\\bin\\Pictures\\butter chicken.jpeg','1)Calories 380\n2)Calories from Fat 89\n3)Total Fat9.9 g 15.2%\n4)Saturated Fat3.6 g 18%\n5)Cholesterol35 mg 11.7%\n6)Sodium680 mg28.3%\n7)Total Carbohydrates60.9 g 20.3%',NULL),(10,'Garlic Bread','1) Preheat the oven to 180°C.\n2) Cut off a thin slice from the bottom side of 2 garlic bulbs, place them cut side upwards on a baking tray, drizzle 1 tsp olive oil on each bulb, sprinkle crushed black peppercorns and paprika powder. Keep the tray in the preheated oven and bake for 20-25 minutes.\n3) Meanwhile, finely chop a few sprigs of parsley and rosemary leaves.\n4) Slice the baguette into thick slices without cutting through.\n5) Take butter in a bowl, add parsley, rosemary and crushed black peppercorns. Squeeze the pulp of the roasted garlic and add it to the butter and mix well.\n6) Apply the butter mixture between each slice of the baguette. Place it on the baking tray, keep the tray in the preheated oven and bake for 15-20 minutes.\n7) Separate the slices and place on a serving platter and serve hot.','1)Garlic bulbs 2\n2) Baguette bread 1\n3) Olive oil 2 teaspoons\n4) Black peppercorns crushed to taste\n5) Paprika powder 1 pinch\n6) Fresh curly parsley a few sprigs\n7) Fresh rosemary 2-3 sprigs\n8) Butter softened 1/4 cup',_binary 'E:\\Workspace\\Java Mini Project\\bin\\Pictures\\garlic bread.jpeg','1)Calories 271\n2)Calories from Fat 32\n3)Total Fat3.5 g 5.4%\n4)Saturated Fat1.8 g 8.8%\n5)Total Carbohydrates52.9 g 17.6%\n6)Protein9.4 g 18.8%',NULL),(11,'French Fries','1) Chop the potatoes:\nTo prepare this easy recipe, you need to make sure that they are cut in the right shape and size. They should neither be too thick, nor too thin and should be cut clean and sharp. The trick is to first slice the potatoes and then cut them lengthwise. You can also use a fries cutter for that long, even shape.\n2) Soak cut potatoes in ice-cold water for 10-15 minutes\nNow, wash the potatoes under running water till they are squeaky clean. Place them in a bowl of iced water for 10 to 15 minutes. Keep them submerged in water or they will turn black.\n3) Deep fry the potato fries\nNow, heat the oil in a deep bottomed pan. Once the smoke starts appearing, reduce the flame and allow it to acquire a lower temperature. Now, deep fry the potatoes in batches. Keep the flame low. This will make them crunchy and also help retain their color.\n4) Sprinkle salt and pepper and serve hot\nDrain excess oil and place them on an absorbent paper. Allow them to cool. Now sprinkle salt and pepper and toss well. Serve immediately with ketchup. They can also be served with burgers and cutlets.\n5) Tips\nTo make those perfect French Fries, add your cut potatoes in ice-cold water for a good 20-30 minutes.\nFor making crispy fries, dry the soaked potatoes twice to thrice in tissue paper and then fry.\nWhen making French Fries for a large gathering, half-fry them and keep aside. When you are about to serve, quickly fry them for a second time and you will have perfect French Frie...','1) 4 Servings\n2) 250 grams potato\n3) salt As required\n4) 1 cup refined oil\n5) 1 and 1/2 pinches black pepper',_binary 'E:\\Workspace\\Java Mini Project\\bin\\Pictures\\french fries.jpeg','1)Calories 319 \n2)Calories from Fat 153\n3)Total Fat17.1 g 26.2%\n4)Saturated Fat4 g 19.8%\n5)Trans Fat4.4 g\n6)Sodium194 mg8.1%\n7)Total Carbohydrates37.5 g 12.5%',NULL),(12,'Chicken Tikka','1) Cut each chicken breast into 2-3 equal sized chunks, trimming off any excess. Wash and leave to drain\n6 chicken breasts\n2) Coat the chicken in the lime juice, ginger and garlic paste and salt. Mix well and leave to marinate in the fridge for as long as you wish - the longer you leave it the more intense the flavour will be\n1 lime\nsalt\n1/2 tbsp of ginger paste\n1/2 tbsp of garlic paste\n3) Add the yoghurt, cream cheese, double cream, coriander stems, ginger, green chillies, black cumin and cardamom powder to a bowl and mix well until combined\n2 tbsp of cream cheese\n3 tbsp of double cream\n3 tbsp of plain yoghurt\n1 tbsp of coriander stem\n1 tbsp of ginger\n1/2 tsp black cumin\n1/2 tsp cardamom seeds\n1 green chilli\n4) Add the marinated chicken, mix again and leave in the fridge for approximately 1 hour before grilling\n5) To cook, thread the chicken onto skewers and grill in a medium-hot tandoor, or over a barbecue for approximately 4 minutes. Turn over and grill for a further 3 minutes or until cooked through\n6) Before serving, sprinkle with chaat masala and lemon juice\n1/2 tsp chaat masala\n1 lemon','1) 6 chicken breasts\n2) 2 tbsp of cream cheese\n3) 1 tbsp of ginger, peeled and chopped\n4) 3 tbsp of double cream\n5) 1 lime, juiced\n6) 1 green chilly, chopped\n7) 3 tbsp of plain yoghurt\n8) 1/2 tbsp of ginger paste\n9) 1/2 tbsp of garlic paste\n10) 1/2 tsp cardamom seeds, ground\n11) 1/2 tsp black cumin\n12) 1 tbsp of coriander stem, chopped\n13) salt\n14) 1/2 tsp chaat masala\n15) 1 lemon, juice',_binary 'E:\\Workspace\\Java Mini Project\\bin\\Pictures\\chicken tikka.jpeg','1)Calories 380\n 2)Calories from Fat 89\n 3)Total Fat9.9 g 15.2%\n 4)Saturated Fat3.6 g 18%\n 5)Cholesterol35 mg 11.7%\n 6)Sodium680 mg28.3%\n 7)Total Carbohydrates60.9 g 20.3%',NULL),(13,'Chicken Biryani','1) Heat oil in a non-stick pan. Add 2 inch cinnamon, 3-4 cloves, bay leaf, 5-6 peppercorns, 2-3 green cardamoms and sauté till fragrant.\n2) Add half the green chillies and sauté. Add onion paste, mix and sauté for 3-4 minutes.\n3)Add ginger paste and mix. Add garlic paste, mix and sauté for 2 minutes. Add khoya, mix and cook till the oil separates.\n4)Add yogurt, mix well and cook for one minute. Add cashewnut paste, mix well and cook for 2 minutes.\n5)Add 1 tablespoon butter and mix well. Add pepper powder, mix well and cook for a minute.\n6)Add chicken, mix well and cook on high heat for 2-3 minutes. Add ½ cup water and mix. Add salt, garam masala powder and mix well. Cook for a minute.\n7)Add remaining green chillies and mix well. Add 1 tablespoon cream and mix well.\n8)Coarsely crush 5-6 peppercorns and add. Switch off heat and add cardamom powder and mix well.\n9)Heat 2 teaspoons ghee in a deep non-stick pan. Add remaining cloves, remaining cinnamon, remaining cardamoms, remaining peppercorns and 1 pinch saffron and sauté till fragrant.\n10)Add rice, salt and 3 cups water, mix well, cover and cook till rice is ¾ done.\n11)Dissolve remaining saffron in a little water and set aside.\n12)Take remaining butter in a bowl. Add remaining cream and saffron water and mix well. Heat in a microwave till butter melts.\n13)Add lemon juice to chicken gravy and mix well.\n14)Heat remaining ghee in another deep non-stick pan. Spread a layer of chicken gravy and top with a layer of the rice. Repeat the step once more with the remaining chicken gravy and rice. Top with fried 