nd into a fine paste along with green chillies.\n3) Cut the paneer into one inch by one inch by half inch pieces. Heat oil in a pan.\n4) Add cumin seeds. When they begin to change colour, add garlic and sauté for half a minute.\n5) Add the spinach puree and stir. Check seasoning.\n6) Add water if required. When the gravy comes to a boil, add the paneer and mix well. Stir in lemon juice.\n7) Finally add fresh cream. Serve hot.','1) Level Of Cooking : Easy\n2) Taste : Mild\n3) Ingredients for Palak Paneer Recipe\n4) Spinach 900 grams\n5) Paneer (cottage cheese) 200 grams\n6) Green chillies 2-3\n7) Garlic chopped 8-10 cloves\n8) Oil 3 tablespoons\n9) Cumin seeds 1/2 teaspoon\n10) Salt to taste\n11) Lemon juice 1 tablespoon\n12) Fresh cream 4 tablespoons',_binary 'E:\\Workspace\\Java Mini Project\\bin\\Pictures\\palak paneer.jpeg','1)Calories : 1350 Kcal\n2)Carbohydrates : 35.4 gm\n3)Protein : 57.2 gm\n4)Fat : 108.8 gm\n5)Other : 0',NULL),(16,'Shahi Paneer','1.Melt the butter in a 5-qt pot over medium heat.\n2.Add chilli,and cook for 2-3minutes stirring occasionally. Add the onion and ginger and cook for 2-3 mins,until fragrant,stirring occasionally. Reduce the heat to low,cover and cook until the onion is completely softened, about 10 mins. Stir occasionally to make sure bottom doesn\'t burn. \n3. Add the tomato puree, stir well and cover again. Cook until tomato looks like it\'s almost separating and is reduced in volume by half about 10 mins.\n4. Add the coriander and paneer masala. Stir well and add the red bell pepper and cook until the pepper is half-cooked,about 5 mins. Add the salt,cover again,and cook for another 5 mins.\n5. Add the heavy cream. Stir well,then add the cubed paneer and cover. Cook for 25 mins all the ingredients are tender.\n6. Garnish with cilantro and serve with naan or rice.\n7. Enjoy.','1) unsalted butter,1/2stick - 4tbs\n2) green chilli, sliced - 2\n3) large onion, finely chopped  1\n4) garlic, crushed - 1tbs\n5) ginger, crushed - 1tbs\n6) 